node.text:
We literally could not be more excited to finally release this video and share how amazing @_lillianbradley is 🥰 Cuddle up, watch this nursery come to life, tell us what you think, then NOMINATE a friend for our next nursery makeover (link in bio!!) 🥳

We couldn’t have done this without the help of our interior designer, @emilytaylordesigns, and so many amazing companies that donated their products to this project!
Wallpaper: @loomwell
1960s vintage rug: @vintagethreadsco
Throw + leather pouf: @woven.nook
Glider: @furnishh_
Bookshelves: @woodyoubuy
Crib sheet: @thebabycubby @copperpearl
Crib pillow: @ebbandthread
@plumandsparrow supplied all the baskets, the Moses basket, bassinet stand, changing basket, macrame wall hanging, and macrame chandelier!
📽 Videographer: @kaitcfilms
#sparrowmamanurserymakeover

node.text:
“I took this picture yesterday morning. After a hard night the night before and in the middle of a rough morning. I was at my breaking point, crying while feeding and texting Chase saying, “I can’t do this.” Because at the time I didn’t want to.

I looked back at this picture after taking it, though, and saw “Mama” written on my shirt. And the chain of my necklace tucked beneath my Mama shirt that says “Eli” on the pendant. And I remembered that I not only CAN do it, but that I AM doing it. And WILL continue to do it.

And that’s right there is what makes motherhood powerful. The ability to rally. The second, third, and fourth wind that we always muster up. That, right when we want to quit, we simply don’t.

The emptiness, tests, losses, and changes all make up a strong, relentless, and powerful new identity: Mama.”

Thank you for these beautiful works, @fittestcore 🤍 and for reminding us that we CAN do it, and we ARE doing it!

Ever wondered how restocks work at Plum + Sparrow? 🤔
A few times a year, we get a shipment of handmade baskets from Africa. Because each basket gets a lot of love and care, we can’t release them all at once. We release the baskets that are completely prepped every Friday at 7am pst! We post on our stories every Thursday announcing which baskets we will restock the next morning 🤍
